===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{lb|en|conjunctive}} For that or this [[purpose]], referring to something previously stated.
#* {{RQ:Authorized Version|Luke|14|20}}
#*: I have married a wife, and '''therefore''' I can not come.
#* {{RQ:Authorized Version|Matthew|19|27}}
#*: Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed thee; what shall we have '''therefore'''?
# {{lb|en|conjunctive}} [[consequently|Consequently]], by or in consequence of that or this [[cause]]; referring to something previously stated.
#: ''Traditional values still have a place, '''therefore''' they will never lose relevance.''
#* {{quote-book|year=1637|author={{w|René Descartes}}|title={{w|Discourse on the Method}}
|passage=Je pense, donc je suis (I think, '''therefore''' I am)}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}
|title={{w|The Celebrity}}|chapter=1
|passage=In the old days, to my commonplace and unobserving mind, he gave no evidences of genius whatsoever. He never read me any of his manuscripts,&nbsp;{{...}}, and '''therefore''' my lack of detection of his promise may in some degree be pardoned.}}
#* {{quote-magazine|year=2012|month=March-April|author=[[w:Terry Sejnowski|Terrence J. Sejnowski]]
|volume=100|issue=2|page=171|magazine={{w|American Scientist}}
|title=[http://www.americanscientist.org/bookshelf/pub/well-connected-brains Well-connected Brains]
|passage=Creating a complete map of the human connectome would '''therefore''' be a monumental milestone but not the end of the journey to understanding how our brains work.}}
#* {{rfdate}}, Spectator
#*: He blushes; '''therefore''' he is guilty.

